laboratory_examinations.findings: Reported as adenocarcinoma with papillary features; Satisfactory for evaluation but limited by drying artifact and obscuring blood. Rare papilliform and elongated ramifying structures identified, with a high nuclear:cytoplasmic ratio.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Initially reported as adenocarcinoma, but two subsequent cervical biopsies showed only inflammatory and reactive changes.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Two consecutive samples demonstrated shedding and proliferative phase endometrium with no evidence of neoplasia.
Demonstrated a diploid phenotype with an S-phase fraction of 7.6%.
